Package com.github.jeuxjeux20.orderedmultibinders.binding

Class OrderedBinding

java.lang.Object
com.github.jeuxjeux20.orderedmultibinders.binding.OrderedBinding
public final class OrderedBinding
extends Object
Represents an ordered binding with an identifier, its actual binding and its @Order annotation.

This is an immutable class, and a builder is available to create a new instance or create a new object based off another instance's values (using builder(OrderedBinding) or change(Consumer)).

Two ordered bindings are considered equal if their identifier is the same (see equals(Object)).

    • change

      public OrderedBinding change​(Consumer<? super OrderedBinding.Builder> builderConsumer)
      Creates a new builder based off this ordered binding, then runs the specified consumer with the builder created earlier, and returns the result of the builder.

      Example: 

      OrderedBinding newBinding = orderedBinding.change(its -> its.identifier(someType));
      Parameters:
      builderConsumer - the consumer which will be run to apply modifications to the builder
      Returns:
      the result of the builder
